<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.24/2–547: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-05T16:00:00-05:00">February
                                    5, 1947—4 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>180. For Ambassador. <gloss target="#t_reDeptel1">ReDeptel</gloss> 83,
                            January 17, 7 p. m. Formal Advice of cessation of deliveries under
                            pipeline given Eremin of Soviet Government Purchasing Commission by
                            letter from Lane dated 1/30/47. However, items to which title had been
                            transferred prior to December 31, 1946 including items “deemed”
                            transferred in accordance with Agreement of Oct 15, 1945 have been
                            released for immediate shipment. Best estimates indicate materials
                            released amount to $9 million.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>